        en: "Juvederm is one of the world's most clinically studied fillers: over 16 million procedures in 20 years, hundreds of published clinical studies, a confirmed safety profile. But contraindications exist for any injectable.\n\nAbsolute contraindications:\n— pregnancy and breastfeeding;\n— hypersensitivity to hyaluronic acid or lidocaine;\n— active inflammation in the injection zone;\n— active infections (including active herpes, especially for lip zones);\n— autoimmune flare-ups;\n— clotting disorders;\n— active-phase oncology.\n\nRelative contraindications (procedure possible with caution):\n— anticoagulant therapy — requires discussion with your treating doctor;\n— tendency to keloid scarring;\n— recent dental implants (1-month interval);\n— recent laser resurfacing or peel (2-4 week interval).\n\nPossible side effects: swelling (especially lips) — 2-10 days; bruising — 15-20% of cases; injection-site tenderness — 1-2 days; mild asymmetry in the first days due to uneven swelling (normalises by day 10-14). Rare complications: granulomas, infections, vascular events — effectively excluded with original product, certified technique and an experienced doctor. That's why we always show the original packaging and serial number before the procedure.",
